  Table 1
 ). Influenza A accounted for most (78.2%) of the confirmed influenza cases, although influenza B was detected more frequently than influenza A in 2008 and 2013. The proportion of samples testing positive for influenza A or B varied by year. One-third of samples (33.3%) were positive for influenza in the A/H1N1 2009 pandemic season, almost all of which were confirmed as influenza A. Excluding 2009, the proportion of samples positive for influenza A or B varied between 6.9% and 19.2%.
